What you need to know:

"It's certainly going to be an interesting couple of windows and I think in relative terms, compared to what we've seen previously, some clubs will feel they've got bargains in the transfer market."Whereas previously they might have had to spend upwards of £50 million, a player may be available for £30-40 million based on the situation at the selling club at a specific point in time. It's one to watch with interest."